contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:36.543 --> 02:37.709
Nervous?

02:37.777 --> 02:41.246
[Sighs]
I'd be lying if I said no.

02:41.314 --> 02:44.016
Well, I wouldn't
want you to lie.

02:44.084 --> 02:45.818
- She knows.
- She can't.

02:45.885 --> 02:47.086
She does.

02:47.153 --> 02:48.387
What's holding
on my Swinton merger?

02:48.455 --> 02:49.988
Are you kidding me?

02:50.056 --> 02:52.624
We've been over this, okay?
If she knew, you'd know.

02:52.692 --> 02:54.226
I do know.
The woman barely knows my name,

02:54.294 --> 02:55.461
and she just summoned me
for dinner.

02:55.528 --> 02:56.962
What is so funny?

02:57.030 --> 02:59.565
Watson, Klyman, Gallo,
Goldberg, and Specter.

02:59.632 --> 03:01.934
- Why are you naming--
- The last five senior partners?

03:02.001 --> 03:03.936
Every one of us was taken
to dinner by Jessica

03:04.003 --> 03:05.237
as a first-year.

03:05.305 --> 03:06.872
And now she's taking you,
which means--

03:06.940 --> 03:08.874
- This is a good thing.
- Exactly.

03:08.942 --> 03:10.209
Oh, God.

03:10.276 --> 03:11.310
- What now?
- What do I wear?

03:11.377 --> 03:13.312
Wh-what do I say?
What do I wear?

03:13.379 --> 03:15.681
We can discuss the prom
at recess.

03:15.748 --> 03:17.783
Tell me what the hell's
holding up my Swinton merger.

03:17.851 --> 03:19.318
Oh, it's just
a nuisance suit

03:19.385 --> 03:20.919
that needs to be cleaned up
before we can clear escrow.

03:20.987 --> 03:22.321
I'm all over it.

03:22.388 --> 03:23.822
Why wasn't that
the first thing you told me?

03:23.890 --> 03:25.190
Uh, I thought
I was getting exposed.

03:25.258 --> 03:26.825
This is
a little less important.

03:26.893 --> 03:29.161
My merger--
your panic attack.

03:29.229 --> 03:30.562
Your compassion.

03:30.630 --> 03:32.631
And I didn't have
a panic attack.

03:32.699 --> 03:34.166
I had a legitimate reason
for concern.

03:34.234 --> 03:36.768
Really? Why would she ask you
to dinner just to fire you?

03:36.836 --> 03:38.403
I don't know. A little
movie called <i>Goodfellas.</i>

03:38.471 --> 03:39.838
Did you see it?

03:39.906 --> 03:41.874
Joe Pesci thought he was
getting made--he got dead.

03:41.941 --> 03:43.509
That's your idea
of a legitimate reason?

03:43.576 --> 03:45.477
"Karen!
Where's the money, Karen?"

03:45.545 --> 03:48.113
- Go back to your cubicle.
- Hey, wait a minute. Do you--

03:48.181 --> 03:50.048
do you think that I might get
an office out of this dinner?

03:50.116 --> 03:51.750
A second ago, you thought
you were gonna get whacked.

03:51.818 --> 03:52.985
Now you want an office?
What?

03:53.052 --> 03:54.319
I'm adapting
to changing circumstances.

03:54.387 --> 03:56.688
Huh. Well, maybe you won't be
the worst lawyer

03:56.756 --> 03:58.090
in the history
of everything.

03:58.158 --> 04:00.759
"Put the gun down, Karen.

04:00.827 --> 04:02.361
Karen?"

04:02.428 --> 04:04.530
They never checked.

04:04.597 --> 04:05.731
What do you mean
"they never checked"?

04:05.798 --> 04:08.901
The Internet was not
what it is today.

04:08.968 --> 04:11.370
It was not so easy
to catch plagiarism.

04:11.437 --> 04:12.905
God,
that's awesome.

04:12.972 --> 04:14.606
- [Chuckles]
- Wait a minute.

04:14.674 --> 04:17.009
If you graduated college then,
then that--

04:17.076 --> 04:18.142
that would make you--

04:18.211 --> 04:19.644
Old enough
to run my own law firm.

04:19.712 --> 04:21.380
But you look so young.

04:21.447 --> 04:23.649
- Well, you know what they say.
- Mm-hmm.

04:23.716 --> 04:26.785
- True beauty is ageless.
- Black don't crack.

04:26.853 --> 04:29.354
[Coughs]
That's what I meant to say.

04:29.422 --> 04:32.024
[Clears throat]
Uhhuh.

04:32.091 --> 04:35.594
Well, enough about me.
I want to hear about you.

04:35.662 --> 04:39.831
What was Harvard like?

04:42.368 --> 04:43.702
I was three
when I realized

04:43.770 --> 04:46.438
that I wasn't like
the other kids.

04:46.506 --> 04:50.075
When school started,
it was like a joke.

04:50.143 --> 04:52.444
I didn't take notes.
I never studied.

04:52.512 --> 04:55.147
Every year
people would tell me,

04:55.215 --> 04:58.317
"Next year
you won't get away with it."

04:58.384 --> 05:01.253
Kept waiting for it
to get harder, but...

05:01.321 --> 05:03.355
it just never did.

05:03.423 --> 05:04.790
And Harvard?

05:04.857 --> 05:08.126
I knew it would end.
I mean, it had to.

05:08.194 --> 05:10.495
I thought, "Yeah,"
I'd finally found a place

05:10.563 --> 05:12.698
where I'd be, uh...

05:12.765 --> 05:14.433
exposed.

05:14.500 --> 05:17.736
But it turns out, even
at the mighty Harvard Law--

05:17.804 --> 05:19.938
You weren't the same
as the other kids.

05:20.006 --> 05:23.475
- I know it sounds cocky.
- Not to me.

05:23.543 --> 05:26.144
The fact is, you don't think
of yourself as smart.

05:26.212 --> 05:28.747
You've always had your mind,
it just is what it is.

05:28.815 --> 05:30.415
Yeah,
that's exactly what it is.

05:30.483 --> 05:32.351
I don't think of myself
as smart, you know.

05:32.418 --> 05:34.152
I just think
of everybody else as...

05:34.220 --> 05:37.689
- Idiots.
- Not smart.

05:37.757 --> 05:41.493
That's what
I meant to say.

05:41.561 --> 05:44.363
Why the law?

05:44.430 --> 05:46.231
It's kind of,
uh, personal.

05:46.299 --> 05:48.634
Isn't that why
we're here?

05:54.374 --> 05:55.540
When I was 11,

05:55.608 --> 05:58.343
my parents were
on their way home from dinner,

05:58.411 --> 06:02.247
and they were involved
in a really horrible accident.

06:02.315 --> 06:07.452
And, uh, they--

06:07.520 --> 06:11.156
my grandmother
took me in.

06:11.224 --> 06:15.294
And it wasn't until I was,
uh, much older

06:15.361 --> 06:18.497
that I realized
that we had a case.

06:18.564 --> 06:21.466
See, it turns out
this restaurant...

06:21.534 --> 06:24.503
they kept feeding
this Mr. Fenton drinks

06:24.570 --> 06:27.439
long after they knew--

06:30.276 --> 06:32.878
didn't matter.

06:32.945 --> 06:35.047
I just--

06:35.114 --> 06:39.918
I felt so helpless.

06:39.986 --> 06:42.387
And I didn't want
to feel that way...

06:42.455 --> 06:45.290
ever again.

06:48.227 --> 06:51.697
Harvey was right.

06:51.764 --> 06:53.565
About what?

06:53.633 --> 06:56.568
I hope you brought
your checkbook.

06:56.636 --> 07:00.739
Dinner's on you.

07:00.807 --> 07:05.043
Wait.
What was Harvey right about?

07:18.091 --> 07:19.658
[Door opens]

07:19.726 --> 07:22.294
- How was dinner?
- Free caviar.

07:22.362 --> 07:23.595
What's not to love?

07:23.663 --> 07:24.496
If you want to know
something about me,

07:24.564 --> 07:26.498
you should have just asked me.

07:26.566 --> 07:28.567
Why can't I just be getting
to know Mr. Ross

07:28.634 --> 07:30.268
the way I got to know you?

07:30.336 --> 07:31.670
Because if you're just trying
to get to know him,

07:31.738 --> 07:33.171
you would have told me
about the dinner.

07:33.239 --> 07:36.808
Something's going on,
and I want to know what it is.

07:36.876 --> 07:38.276
An allegation
was made

07:38.344 --> 07:40.011
that Mike Ross
never went to Harvard,

07:40.079 --> 07:42.948
or any other law school
for that matter.

07:43.015 --> 07:46.385
So I had him checked out.

07:46.452 --> 07:48.220
Squeaky clean.

07:48.287 --> 07:50.322
Graduated top
of his class.

07:50.390 --> 07:51.690
So I took him
to dinner.

07:51.758 --> 07:53.592
I wanted
to see what you saw in him

07:53.659 --> 07:54.826
that makes him
so special.

07:54.894 --> 07:57.262
And?

07:57.330 --> 07:59.064
I get it.

07:59.132 --> 08:00.265
He's a total package.

08:00.333 --> 08:03.902
Maybe even the best
of both of us.

08:03.970 --> 08:05.137
I hope this doesn't mean
you're gonna put me

08:05.204 --> 08:06.605
in charge of recruiting.

08:06.672 --> 08:11.276
Not to worry.
You are off the hook.

08:11.344 --> 08:16.515
Harvey,
one more thing.

08:16.582 --> 08:18.483
He might have
checked out clean,

08:18.551 --> 08:21.353
but I know
that kid's full of shit.

08:21.421 --> 08:22.921
Because there may be
a record

08:22.989 --> 08:24.556
of him graduating
from Harvard Law,

08:24.624 --> 08:26.024
but there's no record
of him graduating

08:26.092 --> 08:29.861
from any college anywhere
on the face of the earth.

08:29.929 --> 08:32.197
So I'm gonna give you
the benefit of the doubt

08:32.265 --> 08:34.099
that you didn't know.

08:34.167 --> 08:37.235
Because I don't want to do
what I would do if you did.

08:37.303 --> 08:40.472
And what you're going to do is
fire that goddamn kid.

08:43.509 --> 08:47.112
♪ See the money,
wanna stay for your meal ♪

08:47.180 --> 08:50.449
♪ get another piece of pie
for your wife ♪

08:50.516 --> 08:53.652
♪ everybody wanna know
how it feel ♪

08:53.719 --> 08:57.322
♪ everybody wanna see
what it's like ♪

08:57.390 --> 09:00.292
♪ living in a beehive
of your mind ♪

09:00.359 --> 09:04.229
♪ me and missus
so busy, busy making money ♪

09:04.297 --> 09:05.730
♪ all right

09:05.798 --> 09:11.203
♪ all that time
imagine this ♪

09:11.270 --> 09:12.771
♪ the greenback boogie

